import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Species'] == 'Adelie']['Body_Mass__g_'].dropna(),
                data[data['Species'] == 'Chinstrap']['Body_Mass__g_'].dropna(),
                data[data['Species'] == 'Gentoo']['Body_Mass__g_'].dropna()], 
               labels=['Adelie', 'Chinstrap', 'Gentoo'])
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Species')['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Species'], data['Flipper_Length__mm_'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average flipper length for each species?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Beak_Depth__mm_', 'Sex'])
    male = data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']['Beak_Depth__mm_']
    female = data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']['Beak_Depth__mm_']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.histplot(male, ax=ax, color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Male')
    sns.histplot(female, ax=ax, color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Female')
    ax.axvline(male.mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Male Mean: {:.2f}'.format(male.mean()))
    ax.axvline(female.mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Female Mean: {:.2f}'.format(female.mean()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of beak depth for male and female penguins?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'], data['Body_Mass__g_'])
    plt.axvline(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].median(), color='red', label='Median Flipper Length')
    plt.axhline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='green', label='Median Body Mass')
    plt.xlabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('How does body mass vary with flipper length?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
